# Outside Inn Studios — Tech Infrastructure Reference
**Updated: March 3, 2026 | Living Document**

> Staff-safe reference for streaming architecture, hardware, software, and operational procedures. Credentials stored separately — see Evan for access.

---

## Streaming Architecture

### Two Modes

**Mode 1 — Lo-Fi Radio (default, 24/7)**
A cloud VPS runs a looping video file via FFmpeg and pushes it to Restream, which forwards to YouTube. Runs independently of any local hardware. Evan's laptop can be off, closed, or in another country.

**Mode 2 — Live Stream (when Evan goes live)**
OBS on Evan's laptop pushes to Restream, which forwards to YouTube. The VPS stream is paused during live sessions. YouTube only accepts one encoder at a time — switching between modes causes a brief reconnection blip (a few seconds).

### Stream Path

```
Lo-Fi Radio:
[VPS: FFmpeg loops HoldtLoop.mp4] → [Restream RTMP ingest] → [YouTube @EIWerner]

Live Stream:
[Laptop: OBS] → [Restream RTMP ingest] → [YouTube @EIWerner]
```

### The Handoff (VPS ↔ OBS)

Going live from OBS:
1. SSH into VPS → attach to tmux session → stop FFmpeg → detach
2. Start OBS stream to Restream
3. Go live as normal

Returning to Lo-Fi Radio:
1. Stop OBS stream
2. SSH into VPS → attach to tmux → restart FFmpeg loop → detach

The blip during handoff is unavoidable under the current architecture. A future upgrade (nginx-rtmp traffic controller on the server) could eliminate it — deferred for now.

### Key Infrastructure

| Component | Role | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| DigitalOcean VPS | Runs 24/7 lo-fi loop | Ubuntu 24.04, 1GB RAM, 1 vCPU, NYC3 region |
| FFmpeg | Loops and streams video on VPS | Stream-copies without re-encoding (minimal CPU) |
| tmux | Keeps FFmpeg alive when SSH disconnects | Session named "stream" |
| Restream (Standard) | RTMP relay to YouTube (+ Twitch when added) | Supports 3 channels |
| OBS Studio | Local streaming software | NVENC encoding via RTX 5070 |
| HoldtLoop.mp4 | The lo-fi video file | 1h40m, 1920x1080, 6fps, H.264 + AAC, ~1.28GB |

---

## The Lo-Fi Video File — How It Was Built

**Source material:** 480 PNG frames (1920x1080, sequential: 1.png–480.png) from Marwan Hasnaoui + 1h40m lo-fi music loop (LofiLoop.wav) from Carson Thatcher.

**Step 1 — Build 6fps silent video from PNGs:**
```
ffmpeg -framerate 6 -i "D:\StreamSourceFiles\HoldtAnimationPNGs1\%d.png" -c:v libx264 -pix_fmt yuv420p "D:\StreamSourceFiles\holdt_6fps.mp4"
```

**Step 2 — Loop animation to match full music duration (6000 seconds = 1h40m):**
```
ffmpeg -stream_loop -1 -i "D:\StreamSourceFiles\holdt_6fps.mp4" -i "D:\StreamSourceFiles\LofiLoop.wav" -map 0:v -map 1:a -c:v libx264 -g 12 -keyint_min 12 -c:a aac -t 6000 "D:\StreamSourceFiles\HoldtLoop.mp4"
```
Note: `-g 12 -keyint_min 12` sets a 2-second keyframe interval at 6fps — required by YouTube for "Good" stream health. The initial build omitted this and showed "Poor" health. Rebuild with these flags if the current file is still in use.

**Step 3 — Upload to VPS:**
```
scp D:\StreamSourceFiles\HoldtLoop.mp4 root@[SERVER_IP]:/root/
```

### File Locations

| File | Location |
|---|---|
| Source PNGs (480 frames) | D:\StreamSourceFiles\HoldtAnimationPNGs1\ |
| Lo-Fi Music (original WAV) | D:\StreamSourceFiles\LofiLoop.wav |
| Intermediate (6fps silent) | D:\StreamSourceFiles\holdt_6fps.mp4 |
| Final Loop (video + audio) | D:\StreamSourceFiles\HoldtLoop.mp4 |
| VPS Copy | /root/HoldtLoop.mp4 on VPS |

All local source files stored on SanDisk Extreme 2TB SSD (portable, device-agnostic path).

